      <h3>Nature Made: USP Verification Means What You See Is What You Get</h3>

      <p>Nature Made is the only ashwagandha gummy on this list that carries <strong>USP (United States Pharmacopeia) Verification</strong>. USP is an independent, nonprofit organization that sets public standards for the identity, strength, quality, and purity of medicines, food ingredients, and dietary supplements. A USP Verified mark means the product has been rigorously tested to confirm that it contains what the label claims, dissolves properly in the body, was manufactured under GMP conditions, and is free from harmful contaminants.</p>

      <p>The 300mg dose sits at the lower end of the clinically effective range. A 2019 study published in <em>Cureus</em> found that 300mg of ashwagandha root extract taken twice daily significantly improved sleep quality in adults with insomnia, suggesting that the dose is effective but may benefit from twice-daily administration. For consumers who prioritize ingredient purity and pharmaceutical-grade quality assurance above all else, Nature Made is the unequivocal choice. The $13.99 price tag and widespread availability at every major pharmacy chain make it the most accessible option for first-time ashwagandha users.</p>

