      <h3>Lemme Chill: A Premium Botanical Blend With Celebrity Backing</h3>

      <p>Lemme, founded by Kourtney Kardashian, has rapidly established itself as a legitimate supplement brand by partnering with credentialed formulators and using branded clinical-grade ingredients. The Chill formula combines 300mg of KSM-66 ashwagandha with two complementary botanicals: <strong>lemon balm</strong>, which has been shown in a 2014 <em>Nutrients</em> study to reduce anxiety and improve mood, and <strong>passionflower</strong>, which a 2011 study in <em>Phytotherapy Research</em> found to be comparable to oxazepam (a benzodiazepine) for reducing generalized anxiety symptoms.</p>

      <p>The formulation is genuinely well-designed. The three ingredients target stress from different biochemical angles: ashwagandha modulates cortisol through the HPA axis, lemon balm inhibits GABA transaminase (increasing available GABA in the brain), and passionflower enhances GABA receptor binding. The result is a formula that addresses both the hormonal and neurotransmitter dimensions of stress. The significant drawback is cost: at $0.50 per serving, Lemme Chill is 56% more expensive than Goli while delivering half the KSM-66 dose. The botanical additions are valuable, but the price-to-potency ratio is harder to justify compared to combining a higher-dose KSM-66 product with a separate lemon balm supplement.</p>

